<subSubSection id="3998CC973A51314C45A80F48B5CDBA9A" pageId="7" pageNumber="92" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="66536222DC199C63E1117E0E46CDD0BC" pageId="7" pageNumber="92">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="69C329AC3391B81D20EA99C2DFE4805A" pageId="7" pageNumber="92">
This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="AA370A71FA82963D9160E45BB4BB0A7B" genus="C." lsidName="C. dolichocarpa" pageId="7" pageNumber="92" rank="species" species="dolichocarpa">
<emphasis id="1C2699FD17CAB8EE215148C9033ACCFE" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="92">C. dolichocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="37C8351E8D7638C5707FD491016F433A" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Cyrtandra longifructosa M. A. Johnson and closest relative (C. dolichocarpa) based on molecular phylogeny by Johnson et al. (2017). A C. longifructosa corolla, anterior view B C. longifructosa flower, lateral view C C. longifructosa elongate cylindrical fruits D C. longifructosa axillary inflorescence and young fruits E C. longifructosa shrub habit F C. dolichocarpa corolla, anterior view G C. dolichocarpa flower, lateral view H C. dolichocarpa shrub habit. All photos taken in the field by M. Johnson, with photos of C. longifructosa taken from the type collection." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.91.21623.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174661" pageId="7" pageNumber="92">8</figureCitation>
), but differs in its glabrous elliptic-ovate leaves (vs. moderately pubescent lanceolate-ovate leaves), blades up to 22 
<normalizedToken id="526F1F57AE4B2F5C73BC9C2197BC518A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
9 cm (vs. blades up to 17 
<normalizedToken id="8874F44960158ACE2C620D48D8D8954F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7 cm), petioles 3-9 cm long (vs. petioles 1-4 cm long), deciduous lanceolate bracts (vs. persistent ovate bracts), peduncles 2-4 mm long (vs. 5-10 mm long), pedicels 11-18 mm long (vs. 21-27 mm long), deciduous beaked calyx (vs. persistent cylindrical calyx), and corolla tube 23-29 mm long (vs. corolla tube 36-55 mm long).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
